17th Depravity</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utravis999.showPublicProfile?language=EN>travis999</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/17/01 7:28:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=49.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Language Rant</span><hr size=1> *Its not a bug its a feature*<br>
(bet you've never heard that one before)<br>
<br>
You can only progress 1 point per hour personally i think it should be every 30 mins.<br>
<br>
I think they need to redo the way guild trainers teach languages, basicly if everyone wastes all their points on human, we basicly got a blue server.<br>
<br>
Troll Ogre should learn, Troll Ogre and DS, first by guild trainer instead of Hum-erud etc.<br>
<br>
All Elves, including DE should be taught Elfish, Elder Elfish Dark Elfish and elder Teir Dal first<br>
<br>
Human types Hum Eru Bar should learn those languages plus high Erud<br>
<br>
Shorties next, leaning halfling, dwarfish gnomish...<br>
<br>
Iksar are loners so they should learn Goblin and Froglok, then Troll.<br>
<br>
this will further force more &quot;RP-like&quot; groups<br>
<br>
Even the way it is, in the later game, whoever has spent time learning their language, will be invalualbe to a group, and those with common toungues like Thieves cant will be also good. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uwylderwarrior.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wylder Warrior</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/17/01 8:38:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=49.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Language Rant</span><hr size=1> Just to keep you updated - I petitioned last night and had a chat with the GM that responded.  He confirmed that in his view there is a bug preventing characters from learning languages by interaction with others beyond a certain level. (They can be trained in guilds if the option exists).<br>
<br>
He advised me to spam the /bug report with this every day and told me to ask my friends to do the same until it is fixed.  He said that he was doing the same.  He also told me that there is no indication from developement as to when they will fix this 'feature'  (/grin Travis - are you an IT consultant?). <p><B>Gray</B><BR>
