e GM / Guide you might talk to can't do anything about it.  I'm sure they'd love for people to quit petitioning them, as they have no control whatsoever in fixing any of the bugs.  Use e-mails, Verant boards, and /bug to get the developers to focus on fixing things. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucloudien.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cloudien</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 68<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/28/01 7:37:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=49.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.cloudk.clara.net/storage/zidane2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Language Rant</span><hr size=1> Yep, I don't think many GMs have the initiative to talk to the superiors.<br>
